A: You can use RandomAccessFile to read the last n bytes of a file. Here is an example:
RandomAccessFile raf = new RandomAccessFile(file, "r");
long length = raf.length();
byte[] bytes = new byte[(int) n];
raf.seek(length - n);
raf.read(bytes);
raf.close();

In this code, file is the path to your file, n is the number of bytes you want to read, and bytes will contain the last n bytes of the file.
Please note that the RandomAccessFile.read method will throw an IOException if it tries to read past the end of the file. So you should handle this exception properly.
Also, the RandomAccessFile.seek method will throw an IOException if the specified position is negative or greater than the length of the file. So you should check the length of the file before calling seek.

